headline: Is It Too Late To Consider AMD (AMD) After Its 106% One-Year Surge?

headline: Nvidia Stock Gains. Why It Just Got a China Chips Boost.
summary: Nvidia  stock was rising early Friday following a report that Chinese authorities will permit sales of its hardware in the country.  Nvidia shares were up 1.6% at $187.74 in premarket trading.  Shares were climbing after Bloomberg reported that Beijing has authorized Chinese firms including  Alibaba  to prepare orders for Nvidia’s H200 chips.
